<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#871f78">Originally posted by Angel on 11-03-2000 05:25 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">It's one thing to have most new content geared toward high-level users.  However, it's another to take away good hunting areas for low-to-mid-level characters in order to give a high-level character a lousy quest.

I'm talking about Lesser Faydark.  This used to be one of my favorite spots.  It was plenty dangerous but a wonderful, underused area.

Then suddenly, I started getting killed there every time I tried going there.  (I kept telling my friend, "this is a great area."  About that time a brownie scout came out of nowhere, killing us both.  This happened more than once.)  It turns out, deadly brownie scouts were put on patrol in the middle of the zone, all for a 50-level druid quest.  AN ENTIRE AREA ESSENTIALLY MADE UNPLAYABLE FOR ONE LOUSY UBER QUEST FOR ONE LOUSY CLASS OF 50-LEVEL CHARACTERS.

This violates two concepts that Verant says they support:

1.  I've heard Verant state that they hope everyone doesn't end up playing the same areas simply because they are the best.  Lesser Faydark was a well kept secret, IMHO.  You have to be crazy to go there now.  So now I hunt where everyone else my level hunts.

2.  Verant is anti-spoiler.  If it wasn't for a site "spoiling" for me why I was getting suddenly getting killed, I would never had known what was going on.  In fact, the only way to have a chance in this zone (for someone lower than 50th level) is to get a spoiler map available on the Internet that shows the patrol routes of the deadly brownie scouts.  Before finding this spoiler site, I was ready to quit Everquest altogether after spending hours trying to recover a corpse.  I just thank Tunare that it was my ranger (with sneak, tracking, and hide skills) and not my cleric who kept getting killed there or I might not ever have recovered my corpse.

So, lower level characters had best hunt where everyone else their level hunts or visit a spoiler site before trying anything new if you want to have a chance.

Angel
</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
